<p>When you register it may appear that the courses will conflict but they do not. &nbsp;These classes may be different from what is listed on your degree audit. Register for the classes listed below, not the ones listed on your degree audit.</p>
<p>IF YOU HAVE PROBLEMS REGISTERING FOR COURSES LISTED BELOW, PLEASE SEND AN EMAIL TO&nbsp;<a href="mailto:STAIGERA@BYUI.EDU">STAIGERA@BYUI.EDU</a>&nbsp; &nbsp; BE SURE TO INCLUDE THE COURSE NUMBER, SECTION NUMBER AND YOUR I#.</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Entrepreneurship</strong></p>
<p>It is suggested students begin their entprenuerial emphasis during their 2nd seme</p>
<p>ster of the Junior year after they have completed the 12-credit IBC program. &nbsp;Follow the recommended course sequencing found <a href="http://www.byui.edu/Documents/advising/advising/sequences/ug13/cbc/Business%20Management%20Entre.%20Sequencing.pdf">here</a> in planning coursework.</p>
<hr />
<p><strong style="font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; line-height: inherit;">Finance</strong></p>
<p>All students register for B 401, 410, 428, and 433.</p>
<p>Then, register for your focus area:</p>
<ul>
<li>Advanced Investments (B 411 and B 424) OR</li>
<li>Money and Banking (B 432 and B 424) OR (<em>not offered Spring 2014</em>)</li>
<li>New Venture Finance (B 424D and B 475) (<em>not offered Spring 2014</em>)</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<p></p>
<p><strong>Marketing</strong></p>
<p>All students register for B 439, B 443, B 446, B 448, B 452, and B 453</p>
<p>Then, register for your focus area:</p>
<ul>
<li>B 451 Internet Marketing</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">OR</span></p>
<ul>
<li>B 457 Retailing AND Comm 231A Advertising&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p></p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Supply Chain Management</strong></p>
<p>All students register for B 461, B 466, B 468, and B 478</p>
